I have a sock subscription website which sells socks every month.  In order to customize the  PaidPlans landing page, I have to code the page using the Pay API.

Everything works fine, even the payment goes through.  The only problem is that the  
Pay.startPayment function does not prompt/return a shipping address.  So I don't know where to ship the goods.  The frustrating part is that if you use the regular  Store, the checkout page requires both the billing and shipping addresses.  As far as I can tell, there is no way to modify the lightbox that appears in order to collect more information.

Please let me know if there is indeed a way to import shipping info from the customers using Pay.

A picture of the Pay payment collection lightbox:




Here is the code I am using.  Again, it works, but I just need to add the extra shipping address.


Page Code:



$w.onReady(function () {

 const currentPlanObject = $w("#dynamicDataset").getCurrentItem();
 const planId = currentPlanObject._id;
 const planPrice = currentPlanObject.price;

  $w('#button1').onClick((event) => {

 let user = Users.currentUser;
 let isLoggedIn = user.loggedIn;
 if (!isLoggedIn) {
      Users.promptLogin().then(() => {
        processPlan(planId, planPrice);
      })
    } else {
      processPlan(planId, planPrice);
    }
 });
});

function processPlan(myId) {


    PaidPlans.purchasePlan(myId).then(orderObject => {
      Window.openLightbox("Contact", orderObject)
       .then((goForIt) => {
 if (goForIt) {
         Pay.startPayment(orderObject.PayOrderId);
       }
      });
    })

}



Backend code:



import Data from '-data';

